Sentencas: A mixed ionic and electronic conductor, BaPr0.8In0.2O3 - delta (BPI), was synthesized and examined as a cathode material for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs).
Titulo: A mixed-conducting BaPr0.8In0.2O3-δ cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction analysis revealed that BPI had a perovskite structure and showed satisfactory tolerance to CO2 and H2O and good chemical compatibility with BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1 Yb0.1O3 - delta (BZCYYb) electrolyte.
Titulo: A mixed-conducting BaPr0.8In0.2O3-δ cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Test cells with a single-phase BPI cathode exhibited excellent electrochemical performances, demonstrating a peak power density of similar to 688 mW cm(-2) at 750 degrees
Titulo: A mixed-conducting BaPr0.8In0.2O3-δ cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: C. Furthermore, the cells with a BPI cathode showed very stable power output at a cell voltage of 0.7 V at 600 degrees C over 100 h, suggesting that BPI is a promising alternative cathode for H-SOFCs.
Titulo: A mixed-conducting BaPr0.8In0.2O3-δ cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
